Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reset_macro_place_constraint(25.10)        reset_macro_place_constraint(25.10)

Name
       reset_macro_place_constraint  -  Resets  the macro constraints that are
       honored by the macro placer

Syntax
        reset_macro_place_constraint

       [-help]

       [-array]

       [-avoid_abut_macro_edge_with_pins]

       [-cell_obs]

       [-cpg]

       [-forbidden_space_to_core]

       [-forbidden_space_to_macro]

       [-honor_strict_spacing_constraint]

       [-horizontal_stacking]

       [-instance_orientation]

       [-macro_corner_keepout]

       [-max_io_pin_group_keep_out]

       [-min_space_to_core]

       [-min_space_to_macro]

       [-parallel_run_length]

       [-parallel_run_length_for_stacking]

       [-pg_resource_model]

       [-power_domain_as_core]

       [-same_length_site]

       [-track_adjustment]

       [-vertical_stacking]

       Resets the macro constraints that are honored by the macro  placer.  To
       define  the  constraints  of macros, use the set_macro_place_constraint
       command.

       Note: For 3D designs in Integrity 3D-IC platform, each die carries  its
       own  macro  place constraint information. You must switch to a specific
       die before invoking the reset_macro_place_constraint command.

Parameters
       -array Deletes all the array constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -avoid_abut_macro_edge_with_pins
              Specifies that macro edges with pins should not be abutted  even
              when the macro distance is within the forbidden spacing setting.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell_obs
              Deletes all the cell obstruction constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cpg   Deletes all the cpg constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -forbidden_space_to_core
              Resets the forbidden space to core.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -forbidden_space_to_macro
              Resets the forbidden space to macro.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each reset_macro_place_constraint parameter. For
              a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command:

              man reset_macro_place_constraint

       -honor_strict_spacing_constraint
              Specifies that forbidden spacing and minimum spacing constraints
              should be honored strictly.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -horizontal_stacking
              Resets the maximum horizontal stack depth and the minimum  hori-
              zontal spacing.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -instance_orientation
              Deletes all the instance orientations.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -macro_corner_keepout
              Resets the macro corner keepout constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -max_io_pin_group_keep_out
              Deletes  the  macro-only blockages which are automatically added
              to IO pins and resets the maximum height or width of  macro-only
              blockages to 0.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -min_space_to_core
              Resets the minimum space to core.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -min_space_to_macro
              Resets the minimum space to macro.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -parallel_run_length
              Resets the parallel run length to enable space checking.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -parallel_run_length_for_stacking
              Resets the stacking parallel run length.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pg_resource_model
              Deletes the pg resource model constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -power_domain_as_core
              Resets power domain as core mode.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -same_length_site
              Resets the minimum difference site number.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -track_adjustment
              Deletes all the track adjustment.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -vertical_stacking
              Resets the maximum vertical stack depth and the minimum vertical
              spacing.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command  deletes all the pg resource model constraints:

       reset_macro_place_constraint -pg_resource_model

